<date id="902A3ECA51441829FD1FF8BAED901B78" box="[646,680,1829,1855]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V7</date>
pale yellow (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51441829FCDCF8BAECDF1B78" box="[837,999,1828,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Figs 383, 385</figureCitation>
); basal abdominal tergites mid brown; T7 and 8 yellow (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51441829FEF8F8D6EEFC1B23" box="[353,452,1865,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Fig. 386</figureCitation>
). Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51441829FDCEF8D6ED831B24" box="[599,699,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
): anterior margin scarcely produced and rounded; lateral margins approach convex sided (B&gt; A, C); pronotal width slightly less than humeral width. Elytron: subparallel sided; interstitial lines not prominent. Head: GHW 
<date id="902A3ECA51441829FDE9F80EEDAA1BEC" box="[624,658,1937,1963]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">6 x</date>
SIW; ASD subequal to ASW.Antennae: incomplete, visible segments are elongate slender. Mouthparts: apical labial palpomere laterally flattened of the form of a wide triangle with inner edge dentate. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51441829FE42F846ED451BB4" box="[475,637,2008,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Figs 385−387</figureCitation>
): well defined apically rounded MPP present; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51441829FB49F846EBCA1BB4" box="[1232,1266,2009,2035]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V7</date>
does not reach lateral margins nor into MPP; dorsal surface of 
<date id="902A3ECA51BA18D7FD3AFF06EDFD1CF4" box="[675,709,153,179]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">V7</date>
not investigated. T8 (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FC2CFF06EB201CF4" box="[949,1048,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 387</figureCitation>
): not subparallel sided, lateral margins widening then converging gently, median posterior margin broadly and shallowly emarginated; anterolateral prolongations longer than posterior entire part of T8 and expanded vertically, without ventrally directed pieces at their bases. Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FE46FE9AED451D58" box="[479,637,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Figs 389, 390</figureCitation>
): posterior margin of sheath tergite slightly sinuous; anterior 6/7 of sternite very narrow, expanding in apical 1/7 with lateral sclerotized pieces of sternite apically divergent, apical margin slightly sinuous, and terminated by paired apically bulbous hairy lobes; posterior margin of sheath tergite slightly sinuous with acute posterolateral corners. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FD6BFEEEECAD1DCC" box="[754,917,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 382−393" captionStartId="128.[151,264,1886,1911]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,166,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@128.[151,1435,166,1866]" captionTargetPageId="128" captionText="FIGURES 382−393. Pygoluciola calceata comb. nov. 382, 383, 384, 388 holotype male (MNHN); 385−387, 389−393 Nilgiri Hills male (NHML). 382, 384 habitus dorsal (384 pronotum only); 385, 386 abdomen: 385 ventral; 386 dorsal; 387 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained; 388 type label; 389, 390 aedeagal sheath ventral: 389−393 aedeagus: 391 ventral; 392 left lateral; 393 dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508250/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Figs 391−393</figureCitation>
): elongate narrow, widest across bases of LL; ML extending only half the length of the aedeagus; LL elongate, extending well beyond ML apex and membranous; darker entire base of LL separated along its mid dorsal line for about 1/3 its length; anterior dorsal margin of LL asymmetrical produced on its left side; dissection of specimen in IRNSB had apically membranous portions of LL folded at about half their length and inclining ventrally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
