<subSubSection id="AC8E4B8151BA18D7FF5EFDBAEDCB1E88" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51BA18D7FF5EFDBAEDCB1E88" blockId="129.[151,1437,153,719]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FF5EFDBAEE0C1E78" bold="true" box="[199,308,549,575]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Remarks</emphasis>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51BA18D7FE29FDBAED461E07" author="Damoiseau" box="[432,638,549,576]" firstAuthor="Damoiseau" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref115869" refString="Damoiseau, R. (1967) Liste du materiel typique conserve dans les collections entomologiques de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique Coleoptera 1 - famille des Lampyridae. Bulletin Institut Royale des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, 43 (8), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1967">Damoiseau (1967)</bibRefCitation>
did not record a type of this species at IRNSB the similarity of the label data and the identification by Olivier of the single male in IRNSB suggests it could be considered a 
<typeStatus id="3B2FA6A851BA18D7FB74FDD6EA701E24" box="[1261,1352,585,611]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">syntype</typeStatus>
. This is a distinctive species with some similarities especially in colour to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951BA18D7FCECFDF2ECCC1EC0" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[885,1012,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerata">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FCECFDF2ECCC1EC0" box="[885,1012,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Abs. cerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has a full LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51BA18D7FB6EFDF2EA211EC0" box="[1271,1305,621,647]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">V7</date>
reaching to all margins, and no MPP. 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51BA18D7FE2DFD0EED471EEB" author="Ballantyne" box="[436,639,657,684]" firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="103 - 139" refId="ref113808" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1968) Revisional Studies of Australian and Indomalayan Luciolini (Coleoptera, Lampyridae, Luciolinae). University of Queensland Papers, Department of Entomology, University of Queensland Press, II (6), 103 - 139." type="journal article" year="1968">Ballantyne (1968)</bibRefCitation>
observed curvature in the LL of several species she assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951BA18D7FADEFD0EEE091E88" authority="" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pygoluciola">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FADEFD0EEAA51EEC" box="[1351,1437,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Luciola</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FF38FD2AEE101E88" box="[161,296,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
and it is probably a post-mortem effect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
